1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:02,330
Greetings everyone.

2
00:00:02,770 --> 00:00:11,350
Today we'll look at the operation of this amplifier attachment for the laboratory signal generator for testing our coils.

3
00:00:12,230 --> 00:00:13,730
There's nothing complicated in it.

4
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:31,930
It's built on the IRF840 transistor, on the heat sink the driver for this transistor TC4420, and a chip mediator between the laboratory signal generator and driver.

5
00:00:32,070 --> 00:00:37,750
The mediator chip is still the same, TC4093BP.

6
00:00:39,350 --> 00:00:48,750
For powering these chips a DC-DC converter is used, built on LM2596.

7
00:00:49,470 --> 00:00:56,410
We set with the help of a trim resistor 15V and use power slightly higher.

8
00:00:56,650 --> 00:01:00,730
In this case my mains converter is 18V.

9
00:01:01,670 --> 00:01:04,290
Can be from batteries, whoever has what.

10
00:01:05,410 --> 00:01:10,050
The device schematic is shown in the picture.

11
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:18,970
By the way, all my schematics under this video I'll post on file sharing and give a link there, which I filmed before this.

12
00:01:20,490 --> 00:01:26,730
At this point we should get such a nice oscillogram.

13
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:30,010
Looking, what else.

14
00:01:30,450 --> 00:01:44,350
The signal from the laboratory signal generator arrives at one of the Schmitt triggers, gets inverted and then we do a second inversion on the second Schmitt trigger to the true signal.

15
00:01:44,410 --> 00:01:53,050
After which through a 10 Ω damping resistor the signal reaches the driver controlling the FET's gate.

16
00:01:53,970 --> 00:02:09,530
And next the FET switches our main power, say from batteries or from any other power source, onto the inductor that acts on our coil.

17
00:02:11,930 --> 00:02:18,910
Wiring isn't complicated, let's look at its operation.

18
00:02:19,850 --> 00:02:25,730
For starters this system connects to the laboratory signal generator.

19
00:02:26,590 --> 00:02:37,870
The lab generator switches to pulse mode, after which the pulse frequency is set on the control.

20
00:02:38,550 --> 00:02:48,950
This schematic of ours is functional up to 2.5 MHz, after which we set signal amplitude.

21
00:02:49,090 --> 00:02:56,670
Signal amplitude is 6 volts, this is the minimum at which this attachment will work.

22
00:02:57,290 --> 00:03:05,890
If you have a 5-volt signal generator, then you'll need to replace this Schmitt trigger chip with 5-volt logic.

23
00:03:06,050 --> 00:03:11,730
It's also compatible with this driver.

24
00:03:12,090 --> 00:03:22,110
Only after this converter on power you'll need to put an L7805 regulator for 5-volt logic power.

25
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:25,250
And the schematic will also be functional.

26
00:03:27,510 --> 00:03:31,630
Set signal amplitude, next we have duty cycle.

27
00:03:31,750 --> 00:03:34,670
Now duty cycle is 73%.

28
00:03:34,670 --> 00:03:36,770
Now I'll show what duty cycle gives.

29
00:03:37,490 --> 00:03:43,530
Feeding power from the power supply to the transistor.

30
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,940
We see the oscillogram.

31
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:56,080
This kind of thing should come out.

32
00:03:57,360 --> 00:04:00,400
And look, now I'll change duty cycle.

33
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:03,460
In this case decreasing duty cycle.

34
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:09,380
Look, the signal becomes unclear.

35
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:22,740
That is, for each little coil we'll need to set individually the signal and the operating point of this transistor at this frequency.

36
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:25,260
That is, duty cycle adjustment.

37
00:04:25,780 --> 00:04:27,980
Here I lowered it to 10%.

38
00:04:27,980 --> 00:04:31,740
Returning to a nice signal.

39
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:40,560
In this case at this frequency at 71% it starts working.

40
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:48,240
After achieving a clean signal, we start investigating our coil.

41
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,000
What do we get?

42
00:04:51,320 --> 00:05:07,900
These coils, with such drive, set the LC resonance frequency for this coil 1.68 MHz, they start working analogous to a Tesla coil.

43
00:05:07,980 --> 00:05:17,620
Now two ends in the air, it's not grounded and you can observe that there's a discharge,

44
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:24,490
that is, analogous to the same little Tesla.

45
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:41,840
The coil works on a quarter wave, can see by glow of the neon bulb.

46
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,760
Closer to the hot end the glow increases.

47
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:58,660
A fluorescent lamp is parallel to the coil, to light it we touch the hot end to its lead.

48
00:05:59,620 --> 00:06:04,840
Connected the hot end and see the lamp burns very brightly.

49
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:08,280
After disconnection the lamp burns dimly.

50
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:12,100
And what should we see on this lamp?

51
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:22,400
Possibly the camera won't transmit now, but on the lamp strips run, that is, the lamp becomes all striped.

52
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:39,120
And if the coil's wound right, these strips will be brightly expressed, and you need to achieve variable frequency on the lab signal generator at the moment when the strips stop completely.

53
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:43,780
If this moment happened, then the coil is made qualitatively.

54
00:06:43,780 --> 00:07:04,580
If you couldn't stop these strips by changing frequency, they'll constantly move, then the coil is made a bit wrong, you don't get a clear longitudinal standing wave around this

55
00:07:04,580 --> 00:07:06,020
coil.

56
00:07:06,780 --> 00:07:17,600
Need to slightly rework it, either increase wire length or decrease, this is a matter of practice.

57
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:37,200
But the main task is for the coil to start, work analogous to a Tesla transformer, both neon bulbs and gas-discharge lamps glow, and the most that needs to be seen, of course is strips on this lamp.

58
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,300
Once more the signal.

59
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:46,100
How to set it, I already showed.

60
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:48,300
And consumption with this.

61
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:54,260
1.32 amps, 12.4 volts.

62
00:07:55,300 --> 00:08:05,300
The better the coil is wound, the less power will need to be fed to the input, and the brighter the lamp will burn.

63
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:13,620
Also the lamp will burn brighter, say, if we connect grounding to this coil.

64
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:21,420
Look, connecting grounding, see that brightness increases.

65
00:08:25,060 --> 00:08:27,060
Without changing power.

66
00:08:29,020 --> 00:08:35,220
We can look on the second probe what's happening.

67
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,160
I'll place it next to the coil.

68
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:46,800
We see what's on the coil.

69
00:08:47,020 --> 00:08:50,460
On the coil at this frequency we have a sine wave.

70
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:56,920
On the sine wave clearly visible strike from the pulse.

71
00:08:58,620 --> 00:08:59,580
Sharp little bump.

72
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:06,800
Now we'll try changing the lab generator frequency.

73
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,200
Changing frequency, going lower.

74
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:12,320
Characteristic feature.

75
00:09:12,380 --> 00:09:29,140
If the coil absorbs your signal well, that is, works coordinated by frequency, these peaks on the inductor, their amplitude will decrease.

76
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:39,620
Look, detuning the system, peak grows, but the amplitude on the coil itself drops.

77
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:43,420
A sign that you're on the wrong frequency.

78
00:09:45,860 --> 00:09:54,840
Returning and the same picture we'll have if we increase the frequency.

79
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:02,740
Same thing, peak grows, signal drops.

80
00:10:03,820 --> 00:10:15,320
We achieve maximum amplitude on the coil and maximum glow of lamps around it.

81
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:20,480
But most importantly, once more, are the strips on this lamp.

82
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:24,680
When you see them, they'll chaotically run.

83
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:28,100
Camera just doesn't show this moment, now they're running.

84
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:30,400
The eye notices very well.

85
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:36,760
Our task is to wind the coil so these strips stop completely.

86
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,460
Good luck everyone in building.

87
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:46,040
Schematic will be posted under the video.
